# TruffleHog Ignore File for PAKE System
# ======================================
#
# This file contains patterns that TruffleHog should ignore during security scans.
# Only add patterns here for confirmed false positives - never for real secrets.
#
# Format: Each line contains a regex pattern that TruffleHog will ignore.
# Use with caution - this can hide real security issues if misused.

# Test environment secrets (confirmed false positives)
test-secret-key-for-testing-only
test-secret-key-for-testing-only-never-use-in-production
test-secret-key-for-testing-only-never-use-in-production-12345678

# Placeholder values (confirmed false positives)
REDACTED_SECRET
placeholder-.*-api-key
changeme-.*-REDACTED_SECRET
REPLACE_WITH_.*
REPLACE-.*-SECURE-.*

# Development environment placeholders (confirmed false positives)
dev-secret-key-change-in-production-
staging-secret-key-replace-me-
dev_password
staging_password

# Test database URLs (confirmed false positives)
postgresql://test:test@localhost
redis://localhost:6379

# Documentation examples (confirmed false positives)
your-super-secure-.*-change-this-in-production
your-.*-api-key-from-.*-console

# Environment variable names (not values)
SECRET_KEY
DATABASE_URL
REDIS_URL
API_KEY
JWT_SECRET

# Test data and fixtures
hashed_password
hashed_REDACTED_SECRET_here
test_token
test-secret

# Common false positives
default
Default
your-
your-.*-change-this-in-production
your-.*-api-key-from-.*-console